  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC COVID-19 Global Appeal West Africa Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC is present in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.drc.ngo/where-we-work/west-africa&quot;&gt;6 countries&lt;/a&gt; in the West Africa Region and has implemented Covid-19 specific activities in all of these countries, despite only receiving COVID-19 specific funding for three of them during the reporting period: &lt;i&gt; Burkina Faso, Central African Republic &amp; Niger &lt;/i&gt;. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt; WASH &amp; Protection &lt;/b&gt; are the sectors with the highest amount of targeted people in this region.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Having adapted its current operations with risk reduction measures to continue providing emergency humanitarian assistance, DRC in West and Central Africa is now adjusting to strengthen &lt;b&gt; Emergency Protection, Food Security, Distribution of non-food items, WASH and Shelter &lt;/b&gt; activities. &lt;br&gt; This scaling up is coordinated with key actors in health and socio-economic responses and benefits from existing networks of community focal points, local teams and know-how acquired in the region focusing on access and resilience employing innovative approaches.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;b&gt; In Cameroon &lt;/b&gt;, DRC is purchasing WASH, PPE, and individual protection assistance kits for victims of protection incidents, commonly targeting children &amp; women. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt; In Niger &amp; Central African Republic &lt;/b&gt;, the focus is on people fleeing conflict who require Shelter and WASH assistance. Some of these programmes have yet to be funded. DRC also provides awareness related to COVID-19 while adressing ongoing needs within Food Assistance, NFI &amp; AVR.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC has received new funding from donors for it&apos;s COVID-19 response. At the same time, many donors have permitted us to re-programme existing grants for our COVID-19 specific work. While for now we are only reporting the financial volume of the new COVID-19 specific grants, we will also report on our re-programmed funds as soon as this information becomes available to us. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt; The OECD DAC CRS Purpose Codes &lt;/b&gt; used to describe this activity refers to the amount of people reached, seen as a percentage of all single instances of beneficiaries reached. This means that it can include double counting, if single individuals have been counted multiple times for different sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
